defaultI had long been aware of comments about the route over Deadman's Hill which being in Nidderdale falls outside the NP boundary. An improvement to the summer Sunday bus service enabled me to visit it about 2 years ago. I was horrified at the enormous depth of the ruts going up the hillside and forming a wide ribbon of erosion. Pressures were being put on North Yorkshire CC to place a permanent 
defaultTRO
